OL,3,CTrain drivers from 16 companies will
OL,4,Cstage fresh strikes in May
OL,6,FAfter almost two years of strikes the
OL,7,Fdeadlock over pay shows no end in
OL,8,Fsight, ITV News Correspondent Charlie
OL,9,FFrost reports
OL,11,FTrain drivers at 16 rail companies
OL,12,Fwill stage a series of fresh strikes
OL,13,Ffrom May 7-9 in their long-running pay
OL,14,Fdispute, the Aslef union has announced.
OL,16,FMembers of the union will couple the
OL,17,Fwalkout with a six day overtime ban
OL,18,Ffrom Monday 6 to Saturday 11 May.
